Durban - Seven people, arrested during a raid at an alleged drug den in Phoenix last Thursday, will make a formal bail application in the Verulam Magistrates Court next week. Kevin Periasamy, his wife Desiree Periasamy and his brother Calvin Periasamy, were arrested at their home in Swallowhaven Road. They, along with accomplices,Â  Shaun Mawesa, Justin William, Jason Alexander and Eric Vuyani Nyawose face a number of charges including drug dealing and possession of drugs. During the raid, police recovered R97 156 in cash, two pistols, a shotgun, 64 live rounds of ammunition, 1 836 heroin caps, 138 heroin straws, 80 large crack cocaine pieces, 30 mandrax tablets, three bags cocaine, two Ecstasy pills and 186g of dagga. According to a police source, the gang, known as the "Bloods" gang, had been allegedly dealing in drugs and are believed to be behind a spate of other crimes, including murder, in the area for many years. The task team had been following up on various leads and pounced on the gang on Thursday morning. They appeared in court on Friday and were remanded in custody while police worked on further investigations. During their court appearance yesterday, they were further remanded in custody and are set to apply for bail next week. Police minister, Fikile Mbalula who was in Durban last week, was shown the haul on Friday by eThekwini North SAPS cluster commander, Major General Lucas Ngobeni who took him through how police busted the gang. The gang is believed to have a network that spans across the country. More charges are expected to be added to the charge sheet. Daily News